6790 6791 6792
Midgaard's High Archive has received formal notification from multiple expedition scouts that the Ash Cult's Western Fold operation is functioning as an intact institutional apparatus, not a scattered religious cell. Senior zealots enforce internal discipline, doctrine-speakers issue formal pronouncements drawn from vent-readings, and an archivist maintains active records of cult activities in the Speaking Vent's name. The High Archive requires engagement data on all three institutional roles before it can classify the Ash Cult as a formal institution subject to civic interdiction rather than a nuisance organization.
The Ash Cult's institutional structure in the Western Fold has been documented and the High Archive has upgraded its classification from nuisance organization to active extra-jurisdictional institution. Midgaard's magistrate court has drafted a preliminary interdiction notice citing the doctrine-speaker's formal pronouncements as evidence of institutional intent and the archivist's active records as proof of organizational continuity. The full interdiction review is scheduled for the next High Court session.
